  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper version: 0.1.0b9\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThe `slice` function seems to only partially validate its arguments:\r\n```\r\n@public\r\ndef slc(a: string[4], s: int128, l: int128) -> string[4]:\r\n    return slice(a, start=s, len=l)\r\n```\r\nFor arguments (\"abcd\", 3, 5) it correctly reverts, however with arguments (\"abcd\", -1, 3) it works and returns all zero bytes, while arguments (\"abcd\", 1, -1) lead to an out-of-gas exception.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nValidate both arguments to `slice`.",
